    public class SVGTextLine
extends SVGG
implements java.util.List<SVGText>
    holds a line for text, including subscripts, etc. assembles SVGText with equal Y into a single line. CHECK WHETHER PHRASE DOES THIS. or see if Phrase should be moved into TextCache

      • splitAtCharacters

        public void splitAtCharacters(java.lang.String splittersString)
        splits each SVGText chunk if it contains any characters in characterString and replaces unsplit string. Thus [abc] with splitters = "[]" will create 3 new SVGTexts Thus [ Thus abc Thus ] The x values are calculated from the bounding box and interpolated. VERY approximate The new values replace the chunk in the list
        Parameters:
        splittersString -
